[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

The Library is a feature located in the right-side panel under the Palette. Its purpose is to provide users with access to a comprehensive list of custom components and template parts. Each type of building block has its own section, and the Library enables users to efficiently find, categorize, tag, and drag-and-drop these building blocks into the designer.

## Available Tab
In the Available Tab of the Library, users can see two main categories: **Custom Components and Template Part References.**

- **Custom Components**: These are globally configured building blocks loaded from the server. In versions 6.4 and older, they were accessible directly under a dedicated section in the Palette.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Template Part References**: These are divided into two types:

**Local**: Defined within the current template.

- **External**: Defined in referenced external templates or template part packages.

Each available building block can be tagged with one of seven different colors or left untagged. Additionally, building blocks can be marked as favorites, making them easily accessible in the **Favourites Tab**.

Users can filter building blocks by name and color tag, with an option to include or exclude custom components from the filter. There is also a toggle to display or hide template part packages, which is particularly useful when there are numerous packages referenced from the current template.

# Favourites Tab
In the **Favourites Tab**, users have access to a personalized list of building blocks they marked as favorites in the Available Tab. This section also allows filtering by building block name and color tag. To remove a building block from the list of favorites, users simply click on the dark star icon.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

# Additional Features
The entire Library section is undock-able, allowing it to be used as a standalone window, similar to other sections. This flexibility enhances the user experience by enabling a more customized and efficient workflow.

Overall, the Library is designed to streamline the process of managing and utilizing custom components and template parts, providing a robust and user-friendly interface for efficient design and development.
